Russian vessel Oleg Naydenov was carrying 1,400 tonnes of viscous fuel oil when it caught fire in Las Palmas port on April 11 .
It was towed out to sea and sank 15 miles south of the island three days later .
Environmental group Greenpeace criticised the decision to tow the vessel out to open sea .
Government activated level 2 alert after analyzing ocean current data from Spain's Oceanographic Institute .